<br>
I suppose Kelethin Legions is no longer considered an rp guild because we have ~gasp~ two dark elves guilded. One's an agnostic dark elf shadowknight, the other a dark elf cleric of Tunare.<br>
<br>
Those race/class combinations can't exist? Oh, I'm sorry. I thought this was the roleplaying preferred server, not the game mechanics preferred server.<br>
<br>
Zinthas defends Felwithe from attack probably more than any paladin other than perhaps Bakanome. I guaran-damn-tee you that Kolyene has better faction with the Church of Tunare in Felwithe than some high elf clerics do.<br>
<br>
I can't speak for Zin, but I enjoy the &quot;you can't be good!&quot; conflict. I enjoy strolling into the Church of the Mother safely when I play Koly. Heck, I enjoyed the faction work. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :\ --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/ohwell.gif ALT=":\"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  I enjoy sitting down with Elia the Pure (Plane of GROWTH faction, cons ally to Koly) and fishing. I enjoy cackling at any evils in my LDoN groups by informing them of the location of the pained unicorn in Lesser Faydark while I ride beside her - fully visible, talking to her as she tells me that she saw a gnoll pup more my speed a few miles back.<br>
<br>
Someone asked me once why I didn't just roll up a high elf cleric, instead of making Kolyene. Where's the challenge in being High_Elf_Cleric_of_Tunare_876? I can point you to plenty of fine rping high elf clerics. I'd rather be Dark_Elf_Cleric_of_Tunare_001, do the faction work, celebrate every time I go up a faction level and be proud that I can walk Felwithe, instead of taking it for granted. Faction work is a bitch too, juts so you know. Everyone says &quot;turn in muffins.&quot; Too freaking easy. I did it the old fashioned way: Crushbone. Once I got that faction up enough, I did turn in a few muffins until I got to the level that I could do the quests that the guildmaster hands out for faction. I think her next project is gonna be Kaladim, Canloe Nusbeck already regards her dubiously.<br>
<br>
IC, I can't stand elves on Venril Sathir faction. I distrust any &quot;good&quot; elf on Venril Sathir faction. It annoys me to no end that Aleyla's spouse is on Venril faction, even if I am beginning to suspect that she is just spying on the Overthere outpost. But guess what? Sharlira is still a &quot;good&quot; elf in the eyes of most good elves.<br>
<br>
He's rping a wood elf beastlord? Interesting concept, I'd give him a little bit of slack and let him run with it.  Enchanters, rogues and bards change their forms all the time, why can't a troll get a crown and claim wood elfness?<br>
<br>
I understand that a lot of people still play the old ruleset. Some of them I count among my best friends. I don't try to push my dark elf members on them. Except Elsbet - I enjoy rping with her as Koly. Koly hears so much about Elsbet around the Stormynytes household that she idolizes her, even though Elsbet considers her lunch. She's determined that she'll make Elsbet her friend one day. It'll never happen, but I have fun playing it.<br>
<br>
And that's what really matters, isn't it? <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.boomspeed.com/kolanifv/kolani_sig.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
